From: OpenWrt <openwrt@openwrt.org>
Subject: [PATCH] netfilter: nft_flow_offload: address review comments (6.12)

Add a short kernel comment for the bridged-path neighbour lookup skip,
document the IPv4 TOS / DSCP flow key in nft_flow_route_routing, and keep
WARN_ON_ONCE when DEV_PATH_BR_VLAN_UNTAG runs without prior encapsulation
while avoiding underflow (follow-up to the BR_VLAN_UNTAG hunk in 675-02).

Signed-off-by: OpenWrt <openwrt@openwrt.org>
---
 net/netfilter/nft_flow_offload.c | 10 +++++++++-
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/net/netfilter/nft_flow_offload.c
+++ b/net/netfilter/nft_flow_offload.c
@@ -102,6 +102,9 @@
 	if (!nft_is_valid_ether_device(dev))
 		goto out;
 
+	/* Bridging fastpath copies Ethernet addresses into ha; do not replace
+	 * them via neighbour lookup on the routed destination device.
+	 */
 	if (!is_zero_ether_addr(ha))
 		goto out;
 
@@ -234,8 +237,11 @@
 				info->num_encaps++;
 				break;
 			case DEV_PATH_BR_VLAN_UNTAG:
-				if (info->num_encaps > 0)
+				if (info->num_encaps > 0) {
 					info->num_encaps--;
+				} else {
+					WARN_ON_ONCE(1);
+				}
 				break;
 			case DEV_PATH_BR_VLAN_KEEP:
 				break;
@@ -356,6 +362,7 @@
 		fl.u.ip4.saddr = ct->tuplehash[!dir].tuple.src.u3.ip;
 		fl.u.ip4.flowi4_oif = nft_in(pkt)->ifindex;
 		fl.u.ip4.flowi4_iif = this_dst->dev->ifindex;
+		/* DSCP from skb TOS field; aligned with nf_flow_table_path.c lookup keys. */
 		fl.u.ip4.flowi4_tos = ip_hdr(pkt->skb)->tos & INET_DSCP_MASK;
 		fl.u.ip4.flowi4_mark = pkt->skb->mark;
 		fl.u.ip4.flowi4_flags = FLOWI_FLAG_ANYSRC;
